.TH FLOWCOIND "1" "March 2026" "FlowCoin Core 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
flowcoind \- FlowCoin full node daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B flowcoind
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
FlowCoin daemon. Runs a full node on the FlowCoin Proof\-of\-Training
blockchain network. Validates blocks, relays transactions, serves the
JSON\-RPC API, and optionally manages a wallet.
.PP
The daemon stores blockchain data, UTXO set, and wallet in the data
directory (default: \fI~/.flowcoin\fR).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-conf=\fR\fIfile\fR
Specify configuration file (default: \fIflowcoin.conf\fR in datadir).
.TP
\fB\-datadir=\fR\fIdir\fR
Specify data directory for blocks, chainstate, and wallet.
.TP
\fB\-daemon\fR
Run in the background as a daemon and accept commands.
.TP
\fB\-pid=\fR\fIfile\fR
Specify pid file (default: \fI.pid\fR in datadir).
.TP
\fB\-testnet\fR
Use the test network (port 19333, HRP \fItfl\fR).
.TP
\fB\-regtest\fR
Enter regression test mode. Blocks can be generated on demand.
.TP
\fB\-listen\fR
Accept incoming connections (default: 1 unless \fI\-connect\fR is used).
.TP
\fB\-port=\fR\fIN\fR
Listen for connections on port \fIN\fR (default: 9333).
.TP
\fB\-maxconnections=\fR\fIN\fR
Maintain at most \fIN\fR connections to peers (default: 125).
.TP
\fB\-addnode=\fR\fIip:port\fR
Add a node to connect to and attempt to keep the connection open.
.TP
\fB\-connect=\fR\fIip:port\fR
Connect only to the specified node(s). No other outbound connections.
.TP
\fB\-dnsseed\fR
Query DNS seeds for peer addresses (default: 1).
.TP
\fB\-server\fR
Accept JSON\-RPC commands (default: 1).
.TP
\fB\-rpcuser=\fR\fIuser\fR
Username for JSON\-RPC connections.
.TP
\fB\-rpcpassword=\fR\fIpw\fR
Password for JSON\-RPC connections.
.TP
\fB\-rpcport=\fR\fIN\fR
Listen for JSON\-RPC connections on port \fIN\fR (default: 9334).
.TP
\fB\-rpcbind=\fR\fIaddr\fR
Bind the JSON\-RPC server to address \fIaddr\fR (default: 127.0.0.1).
.TP
\fB\-rpcallowip=\fR\fIsubnet\fR
Allow JSON\-RPC connections from specified subnet (CIDR notation).
.TP
\fB\-disablewallet\fR
Do not load the wallet and disable wallet RPC calls.
.TP
\fB\-wallet=\fR\fIfile\fR
Specify wallet file (default: \fIwallets/wallet.dat\fR in datadir).
.TP
\fB\-dbcache=\fR\fIN\fR
Set database cache size in megabytes (default: 450).
.TP
\fB\-par=\fR\fIN\fR
Set the number of script verification threads (0=auto, default: 0).
.TP
\fB\-prune=\fR\fIN\fR
Prune block files to a target size of \fIN\fR MB (0=disable).
.TP
\fB\-debug=\fR\fIcategory\fR
Output debugging information for a category. Categories: net, validation,
mining, rpc, wallet, mempool, model, sync.
.TP
\fB\-printtoconsole\fR
Send log output to stdout instead of the debug log file.
.SH FILES
.TP
\fI~/.flowcoin/flowcoin.conf\fR
Default configuration file.
.TP
\fI~/.flowcoin/blocks/\fR
Block data files (blk*.dat).
.TP
\fI~/.flowcoin/chainstate/\fR
Chain database and UTXO set (SQLite).
.TP
\fI~/.flowcoin/wallets/wallet.dat\fR
Wallet database.
.TP
\fI~/.flowcoin/indexes/\fR
Transaction index database (SQLite).
.TP
\fI~/.flowcoin/debug.log\fR
Debug log file.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR flowcoin\-cli (1),
.BR flowcoin\-tx (1)
.SH BUGS
Report bugs at https://github.com/flowcoin/flowcoin/issues
.SH AUTHOR
Haruki Tanaka and The FlowCoin Developers.
